PLANTS OF NORTH CAROLINA

*Galax urceolata* (Poir.) Brummitt
det. Michelle Gaynor, 2 June 2021

WAYNE COUNTY: Cliff of Neuse State Park, Galax trail.
Elev. 27 – 29 m. Co-occurring species include *Sassafras* spp., sweetleaf, and *Hexastylis arifolia*. Flowers old, top of spikelet still in bud. Mix of new and old leaves.
Lat. 35.23682498 Long. -77.883332 Datum: WGS84
coll. Michelle Gaynor # 57 2 June 2021

North Carolina Division of Parks and Recreation, Scientific Research and Collecting Permit, 2021_0524.
Corresponds to genetic sample MLG277 (Pop 20). Only about 4 meters from collection 56.

Ploidy level inferred via flow cytometry: Diploid.
Michelle L. Gaynor 7 Sept 2022
